SENATE BILL 338
P6 6lr2467
CF HB 399
By: Senator Lewis Young (Chair, Joint Committee on Pensions)
Introduced and read first time: January 23, 2026
Assigned to: Budget and Taxation
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 State Retirement and Pension System – Transfers Between Systems –
3 Workgroup – Extension
4 FOR the purpose of extending the reporting date and the termination date for a workgroup
5 convened by the State Retirement Agency to study transfers of member service
6 between State and local retirement and pension systems; altering the entities to
7 which the State Retirement Agency is required to report; and generally relating to
8 transfers of member service between State and local retirement and pension
9 systems.
10 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
11 Chapter 768 of the Acts of the General Assembly of 2025
12 Section 1(a)(1)
13 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
14 Chapter 768 of the Acts of the General Assembly of 2025
15 Section 1(d) and 2
16 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
17 Chapter 769 of the Acts of the General Assembly of 2025
18 Section 1(a)(1)
19 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
20 Chapter 769 of the Acts of the General Assembly of 2025
21 Section 1(d) and 2
22 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
23 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
24 Chapter 768 of the Acts of 2025
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
