2 SENATE BILL 338
1 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
2 That:
3 (a) (1) The State Retirement Agency shall convene a workgroup of interested
4 stakeholders to study the requirements and processes for transfers of member service
5 between State and local retirement and pension systems and make recommendations to
6 improve the process of transfers between systems.
7 (d) On or before [December 1, 2025] OCTOBER 1, 2026, the State Retirement
8 Agency shall submit a report of the findings and recommendations of the workgroup,
9 including the need for any legislative initiatives, to the Governor and, in accordance with §
10 2–1257 of the State Government Article, the [General Assembly] SENATE BUDGET AND
11 TAXATION COMMITTEE, THE HOUSE APPROPRIATIONS COMMITTEE, AND THE
12 JOINT COMMITTEE ON PENSIONS.
13 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect June
14 1, 2025. It shall remain effective for a period of [1 year] 2 YEARS and 1 month and, at the
15 end of June 30, [2026] 2027, this Act, with no further action required by the General
16 Assembly, shall be abrogated and of no further force and effect.
17 Chapter 769 of the Acts of 2025
